.TH "vidtv_memcpy" 9 "vidtv_memcpy" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vidtv_memcpy \- wrapper routine to be used by MPEG-TS generator, in order to avoid going past the output buffer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" vidtv_memcpy
.BI "(void *to "  ","
.BI "size_t to_offset "  ","
.BI "size_t to_size "  ","
.BI "const void *from "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "to" 12
Starting element to where a MPEG-TS packet will
be copied.
.IP "to_offset" 12
Starting position of the \fIto\fP buffer to be filled.
.IP "to_size" 12
Size of the \fIto\fP buffer.
.IP "from" 12
Starting element of the buffer to be copied.
.IP "len" 12
Number of elements to be copy from \fIfrom\fP buffer
into \fIto\fP+ \fIto_offset\fP buffer.
.SH "NOTE"
Real digital TV demod drivers should not have memcpy
wrappers. We use it here because emulating MPEG-TS
generation at kernelspace requires some extra care.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns the number of bytes written
